The paper deals with the problem of cross-view geo-localization, which involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) techniques. The paper proposes a new dataset for drone-based geo-localization, which involves machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The paper also analyzes off-the-shelf CNN features, which is a common technique in CV. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of navigation, which is related to graphics (GR) and robotics (RO) fields. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.GR.
